# The `LLJIT` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

A pre-fabricated ORC JIT stack that can serve as an alternative to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcjit">MCJIT</a>. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

A pre-fabricated ORC JIT stack that can serve as an alternative to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcjit">MCJIT</a>.

Create instances using <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/lljitbuilder">LLJITBuilder</a>.

Definition at line 41 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/lljit-h">LLJIT.h</a>.

### linkStaticLibraryInto() {#aaa681b188079626ba7d773d29128e3bf}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::orc::LLJIT::linkStaticLibraryInto (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> &amp; JD, std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorybuffer">MemoryBuffer</a> &gt; LibBuffer)</>}>
Link a static library into the given <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

If the given <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorybuffer">MemoryBuffer</a> contains a valid static archive (or a universal binary with an archive slice that fits the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/lljit">LLJIT</a> instance&#39;s platform / architecture) then it will be added to the given <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> using a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/staticlibrarydefinitiongenerator">StaticLibraryDefinitionGenerator</a>.

### loadPlatformDynamicLibrary() {#a4ece82000ef0a7c6a9e9947cbdbbd1b9}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; JITDylib &amp; &gt; llvm::orc::LLJIT::loadPlatformDynamicLibrary (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> char &#42; Path)</>}>
Load a (real) dynamic library and make its symbols available through a new <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> with the same name.

If the given <em>executor</em> path contains a valid platform dynamic library then that library will be loaded, and a new bare <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> whose name is the given path will be created to make the library&#39;s symbols available to JIT&#39;d code.
